  "title": "Braai pie - so delicious over the coals - Marinda Kook",
  "description": null
 },
 "html": "<p>The braai pie has no set quantities &#8211; except for the dough.  It's delicious as a side dish or as a starter.  Guests are usually amazed when you make it over the coals.  You'll need a deep-ish toasting grid. The filling is up to your taste.  I'm going to put together two variations.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-090.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-911\" alt=\"braai paai blog 090\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-090-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>NEEDED:</p>\n<p>First Filling:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2 rolls puff pastry</li>\n<li>1/2 tin tomato mixture<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-016.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-892\" alt=\"braai paai blog 016\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-016-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>2 small sausages, ham or bacon</li>\n<li>2 cups cheese of your choice ( I used cheddar)<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-005.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-891\" alt=\"braai paai blog 005\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-005-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>1 wedge blue cheese<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-039.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-913\" alt=\"braai paai blog 039\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-039-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>1 wheel feta cheese</li>\n<li>2 onions</li>\n<li>125ml balsamic vinegar</li>\n<li>80 ml brown sugar</li>\n</ul>\n<p>NOW:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>braai the sausages until brown in the pan and slice them thinly<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-001.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-890\" alt=\"braai paai blog 001\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-001-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>braai the onions with balsamic vinegar and brown sugar in the sausages' pan until it cooks down thick<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-030.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-897\" alt=\"braai paai blog 030\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-030-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>sprinkle flour on a baking tray and lay the one sheet of dough on the tray  &#8211; as you start stacking the layers, leave about a centimetre strip open all the way round the dough<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-017.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-893\" alt=\"braai paai blog 017\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-017-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>spread half of the tomato mixture on the dough<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-021.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-895\" alt=\"braai paai blog 021\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-021-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>place the sausages on the tomato layer<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-025.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-896\" alt=\"braai paai blog 025\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-025-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>now layer the onions on the sausage layer<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-035.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-898\" alt=\"braai paai blog 035\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-035-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>sprinkle the cheddar cheese over the sausages</li>\n<li>now crumble the blue cheese and feta right on top<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-045.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-900\" alt=\"braai paai blog 045\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-045-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>close it all up with the other roll of dough<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-048.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-901\" alt=\"braai paai blog 048\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-048-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>press the edges together with a fork<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-049.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-902\" alt=\"braai paai blog 049\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-049-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>make a fire and braai the pie<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-066.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-906\" alt=\"braai paai blog 066\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-066-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>don't clamp the grid too tightly &#8211; use the two sides only to help you turn it over<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-068.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-907\" alt=\"braai paai blog 068\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-068-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>once it's nicely browned on both sides, it's ready to eat<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-081.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-908\" alt=\"braai paai blog 081\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-081-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>ALTERNATIVE &#8211; for braaibroodjie</p>\n<p>Second Filling:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>take one sheet of dough and sprinkle cheese over &#8211; only on the one half, because you're going to fold it over<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-056.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-903\" alt=\"braai paai blog 056\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-056-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>slice tomato on top of the cheese and salt and pepper to taste<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-059.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-904\" alt=\"braai paai blog 059\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-059-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>slice onions thinly and layer on top of the tomato<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-062.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-905\" alt=\"braai paai blog 062\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-062-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>fold the dough closed and press it firm with a fork all around the edges</li>\n<li>now braai it gently over the coals<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-083.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-909\" alt=\"braai paai blog 083\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-083-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Let me tell you, it's so good that your guests will come back for more.  The filling can be anything your heart desires &#8211; just do it!<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-086.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-910\" alt=\"braai paai blog 086\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/braai-paai-blog-086-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
 "recipe": null
